DETAIL.ABOUT_US:
About the Project

The addressed problem:

Every year millions of meritorious, talented & needy students belonging to underprivileged or underserved communities unable to access quality education due to financial constraints. This is further leading to increase in voluntary dropout rate in last mile schools & colleges. On a contrary note, more than INR 16000+ Crore worth of educational scholarships are available for Indian students every year specially for girl child & students belonging to minority, SC, ST, OBC, BPL communities. Significant amount of it, remain undisbursed due to lack of applicants. Unfortunately, less than 10% of students are aware of the available scholarships.

Last-mile scholarship delivery is a challenge, as government organizations, corporates & philanthropists have no expertise and technology capability to do so. They also lack transparency resulting misappropriation of funds.

Approach to Solve:

Student to Scholar Program (S2S) is a unique initiative led by Michael & Susan Dell Foundation in association with Buddy4Study to aware & assist students about available scholarships through on-ground mobilisation with a vision to ensure access to quality education for all students belonging to underserved communities of Haryana, Delhi and UP.
